name: DeAndre Hopkins
summary: The Tennessee Titans have traded wide receiver DeAndre Hopkins to the Kansas City Chiefs. The move comes after years of speculation about Hopkins' future with the Titans. Hopkins, a three-time All-Pro, has been one of the most productive receivers in the NFL since he entered the league in 2013. However, his production declined in recent years, and he was due a large contract extension. The Chiefs, who have been looking to add a veteran receiver, were able to acquire Hopkins for a relatively low price. The trade is expected to benefit both teams. The Chiefs get a proven star receiver who can help them compete for a Super Bowl. The Titans get salary cap relief and a chance to rebuild their offense.

name: Andy Dalton
summary: Carolina Panthers quarterback Andy Dalton was involved in a car accident in Charlotte, North Carolina. Dalton was driving the vehicle with his family and dog inside. No one involved in the accident required emergency medical transport. However, Dalton is being evaluated by the Panthers' medical staff. As a result of the accident, Bryce Young will start at quarterback for the Panthers in Week 8.
